definitions.definition: An antigenic enzyme , found on the surfaces of viruses , that catalyzes the hydrolysis of terminal acylneuraminic residues from oligosaccharides , glycoproteins , and glycolipids .

main_definition: ( biochemistry ) An antigenic enzyme , found on the surfaces of viruses , that catalyzes the hydrolysis of terminal acylneuraminic residues from oligosaccharides , glycoproteins , and glycolipids .
